Online payments and billing platform DirectPay Online Group has acquired South Africa&rsquo;s cloud-based payment gateway PayThru which specialises in integration of mobile devices. This comes a year after Direct Pay began the entry into South Africa in September last year by merging with PayGate, a leading online payments processor with presence in 24 African markets.DPO Group chairman Offer Gat said the acquisition is in line with the group&rsquo;s strategy to strengthen its positioning in South Africa and establish itself as the leading payment service provider in the continent.&ldquo;Investing in market leading businesses in the online payments space is a core pillar of our growth strategy, our vision is to provide one payment solution across Africa and this acquisition brings us one step closer to that goal,&rdquo; Gat said.